  "response": "Electric (AEG) and gas airsoft guns have some key differences:\n\nElectric Airsoft Guns (AEGs):\n- Use rechargeable battery\n- More consistent shot performance\n- Generally lower maintenance\n- Better in cold weather\n- More affordable long-term\n- Typically used in assault rifles and other primary weapons\n\nGas Airsoft Guns:\n- Powered by compressed gas (CO2 or green gas)\n- More realistic blowback action\n- Better performance in warm weather\n- Higher recoil and more realistic feel\n- Often used in pistols and some rifles\n- May require more frequent maintenance\n- Performance can vary with temperature\n\nEach type has pros and cons, and choice depends on personal preference and playing style.",
